<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<qti-assessment-item
    xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0"
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0p1_v1p0.xsd http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/mathml/v3p0/schema/xsd/mathml3.xsd"
    identifier="cross-price-elasticity-formula"
    title="Cross-Price Elasticity Formula"
    time-dependent="false"
    xml:lang="en-US">

    <qti-response-declaration base-type="identifier" cardinality="single" identifier="RESPONSE">
        <qti-correct-response>
            <qti-value>D</qti-value>
        </qti-correct-response>
    </qti-response-declaration>


    <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
    <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>

    <qti-item-body>
        <div id="reference_text">
            <p>Suppose an economist wants to calculate how responsive the quantity demanded of good 
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                    <mi>X</mi>
                </math> is in response to a change in the price of good 
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                    <mi>Y</mi>
                </math>.
            </p>
        </div>
        <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1" min-choices="1" class="qti-orientation-vertical">
            <qti-prompt>Which of the formulas below would be a correct formula to use if we wanted to calculate the cross-price elasticity of demand for good <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>X</mi></math> and good <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>Y</mi></math>?</qti-prompt>
            <qti-simple-choice identifier="A">
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                    <mfrac>
                        <mrow>
                            <mo>%</mo>
                            <mi>Δ</mi>
                            <msub>
                                <mi>Q</mi>
                                <mi>X</mi>
                            </msub>
                        </mrow>
                        <mrow>
                            <mo>%</mo>
                            <mi>Δ</mi>
                            <msub>
                                <mi>P</mi>
                                <mi>X</mi>
                            </msub>
                        </mrow>
                    </mfrac>
                </math>
                <qti-feedback-inline outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" identifier="A">This is the formula that would be use to calculate the elasticity of demand for good <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>X</mi></math> in response to its own price.</qti-feedback-inline>
            </qti-simple-choice>
            <qti-simple-choice identifier="B">
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                    <mfrac>
                        <mrow>
                            <mo>%</mo>
                            <mi>Δ</mi>
                            <msub>
                                <mi>Q</mi>
                                <mrow>
                                    <mi>X</mi>
                                    <mn>1</mn>
                                </mrow>
                            </msub>
                        </mrow>
                        <mrow>
                            <mo>%</mo>
                            <mi>Δ</mi>
                            <msub>
                                <mi>Q</mi>
                                <mrow>
                                    <mi>Y</mi>
                                    <mn>1</mn>
                                </mrow>
                            </msub>
                        </mrow>
                    </mfrac>
                </math>
                <qti-feedback-inline outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" identifier="B">This says how responsive one quantity is to a change in another quantity, but we want to know how responsive one quantity is to a change in another good's price.</qti-feedback-inline>
            </qti-simple-choice>
            <qti-simple-choice identifier="C">
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                    <mfrac>
                        <mrow>
                            <mo>%</mo>
                            <mi>Δ</mi>
                            <msub>
                                <mi>Q</mi>
                                <mi>Y</mi>
                            </msub>
                        </mrow>
                        <mrow>
                            <mo>%</mo>
                            <mi>Δ</mi>
                            <msub>
                                <mi>P</mi>
                                <mi>Y</mi>
                            </msub>
                        </mrow>
                    </mfrac>
                </math>
                <qti-feedback-inline outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" identifier="C">This is the formula that would be use to calculate the elasticity of demand for good <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>Y</mi></math> in response to its own price.</qti-feedback-inline>
            </qti-simple-choice>
            <qti-simple-choice identifier="D">
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                    <mfrac>
                        <mrow>
                            <mo>%</mo>
                            <mi>Δ</mi>
                            <msub>
                                <mi>Q</mi>
                                <mi>X</mi>
                            </msub>
                        </mrow>
                        <mrow>
                            <mo>%</mo>
                            <mi>Δ</mi>
                            <msub>
                                <mi>P</mi>
                                <mi>Y</mi>
                            </msub>
                        </mrow>
                    </mfrac>
                </math>
                <qti-feedback-inline outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" identifier="D">This shows how the quantity of <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>X</mi></math> will respond to a change in the price of good <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>Y</mi></math>.</qti-feedback-inline>
            </qti-simple-choice>
            <qti-simple-choice identifier="E">
                <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
                    <mfrac>
                        <mrow>
                            <mo>%</mo>
                            <mi>Δ</mi>
                            <msub>
                                <mi>Q</mi>
                                <mi>Y</mi>
                            </msub>
                        </mrow>
                        <mrow>
                            <mo>%</mo>
                            <mi>Δ</mi>
                            <msub>
                                <mi>P</mi>
                                <mi>X</mi>
                            </msub>
                        </mrow>
                    </mfrac>
                </math>
                <qti-feedback-inline outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK-INLINE" identifier="E">This shows how the quantity of <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>Y</mi></math> will respond to a change in the price of good <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>X</mi></math>, but we want to know how <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>X</mi></math> responds to changes in the price of good <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>Y</mi></math>.</qti-feedback-inline>
            </qti-simple-choice>
        </qti-choice-interaction>
        
        <qti-feedback-block outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" identifier="CORRECT" show-hide="show">
            <qti-content-body>
                <p><strong>Correct!</strong> Cross-price elasticity of demand measures how the quantity demanded of one good (<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>X</mi></math>) responds to changes in the price of another good (<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>Y</mi></math>). The formula shows the percentage change in quantity of <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>X</mi></math> divided by the percentage change in price of <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>Y</mi></math>.</p>
            </qti-content-body>
        </qti-feedback-block>
        <qti-feedback-block outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK" identifier="INCORRECT" show-hide="show">
            <qti-content-body>
                <p><strong>Not quite.</strong> Remember that cross-price elasticity measures how one good's quantity responds to another good's price change. Look for the formula that has the quantity of good <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>X</mi></math> in the numerator and the price of good <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>Y</mi></math> in the denominator.</p>
            </qti-content-body>
        </qti-feedback-block>
    </qti-item-body>

    <qti-response-processing template="https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/rptemplates/match_correct"/>

</qti-assessment-item>